node.text: American families are getting the support they need, starting this week. This will reduce child poverty by over 50%! Nearly all families with kids will qualify. And when families do well, the economy does well. For every $1 we invest in families, we see $8 returned into the economy. So this helps everyone. I’m deeply grateful for Congresswoman DeLauro’s work on getting this policy enacted, and deeply grateful to President Biden for prioritizing families and uplifting so many! Here we go!! Visit www.ChildTaxCredit.gov to figure out what you’ll begin receiving this month!

node.text: Today I’m joined by two of my ocean heroes, Dr. Ayana Elizabeth Johnson and Philippe Cousteau, to discuss why our current climate crisis must be taken seriously, but also fills us with optimism and inspiration. Hint: young people have a lot to do with solutions! Change and community uplift and economic empowerment and cultural wealth are all possible when we prioritize climate! So let’s goooo 🤍💙

node.text: [CONT’D 2] Jared Yates Sexton rightly pointed out that “The entire reason we have rules to expel members of Congress is to expel members of Congress who have openly endorsed the murder of their colleagues, traffic in racist, virulent conspiracy theories, and have worked to overthrow the government.” That day? Over 140 officers injured. Two officers are dead from the attack; two from suicide. Officers without helmets sustained brain injuries. One officer has two cracked ribs and two smashed spinal discs. One officer is going to lose his eye; one was stabbed with a metal fence stake. And people like Lauren Boebert gave tours?! Greene says these are patriots?? Ted Cruz spoke at the rallies screaming “don’t go quietly!!” Madison Cawthorn told supporters “you can threaten” your reps over the election. Don’t even get me started on Josh Hawley. And these are the same people, who despite having facts about @ayannapressley’s panic buttons having been ripped out of her Congressional office ahead of the attack, despite the published evidence that Christopher Miller, Trump's then-acting defense secretary, on Jan 4 issued a memorandum stating that authorities at the Capitol were not allowed to use weapons, wear helmets or body armor, interact physically with protestors, employ riot control agents, or even make arrests, essentially guaranteeing that the insurrection would succeed, want to move on!? You’re damn right I agree with Rep @jackiespeier that inciting insurrection and being a terrorist sympathizer in the halls of Congress or the Senate means you should be labeled as such. But what Breitbart did, falsely claiming I am “advocating for labeling [ALL] Republicans as terrorists,” misrepresenting my agreement with Congressional leaders about the standard to which their colleagues are held and obfuscating my point to claim I’m apparently passing judgment on anyone who’s ever voted as a registered conservative? It’s egregious and irresponsible. It lacks context or the critical thinking skills required to make nuanced points. But the thing is?? They know that. “News” editors do pay attention, and do know what the argument is. [CONT]

node.text: I met Lauren Underwood years ago when she was running for Congress in Illinois’ 14th district. She is a powerhouse! A registered nurse and health policy expert, Lauren has the hands-on knowledge we need from leadership to prioritize our communities, especially during a pandemic! She served as a Senior Advisor to the US Department of Health and Human Services in the Obama Administration, and helped communities across the country achieve broader access to Medicare, improve healthcare quality, and worked to reform private insurance. When she won her election in 2018, she did so historically by winning every single county in the district! She is the youngest Black woman ever elected to Congress! And she is crushing it! She’s introduced 42 pieces of legislation, passed 15 out of the House, and had 3 pieces of bipartisan legislation signed into law so far. She’s a hero and a leader, and someone I just love spending time with! Today we are sending lots of love and encouragement to voters in #Illinois, #California, and everywhere else as we head into #electionday! #BidenHarris2020 💙

The #ChildTaxCredit checks that go out today will lift over 50% of American children out of poverty. No matter where you’re from, or how you vote. The Biden Administration is changing the lives of American families. Thank you to everyone who has fought for this. @potus. @rosa_delauro. @senatedems. And everyone else.

NOT ONE Republican voted for this. Not one. But we got it done anyhow. Never forget that, families. Remember who is showing up for you and your kids. You pay taxes. You invest in this country. And you deserve an ROI on that investment, and support from your country as you strive to succeed, create, and grow. Period. This will change lives. This is the best of us.

・・・

The #, from @katiegrossbard:
💰 The White House says $15 billion in payments have been sent out to the families of nearly 60 million children. Families will receive the funds by direct deposit or check. How much you get will depend on income and number of eligible children.

🗣 It's a huge undertaking by the IRS. The @whitehouse is describing the one-year expansion as historic relief to the largest number of working families ever.

💸 For every child under the age of 6, families will get up to $3,600 under the expansion, or $300 per month. For every child between 6-17, the amount is $3,000, or $250 per month. This is a significant increase from past years when the credit was $2,000 per child, ages 0-16. 

🤓 What's being sent out this week is known as an advance child tax credit payment. If you file federal taxes, you should automatically get the monthly payments.

@npr @nprpolitics #childtaxcredit #childpoverty #americanrescueplan #biden

node.text:
The incomparable Ibram X. Kendi (@ibramxk) sat down with me on @workinprogress this week, and together we dove into the topics at the heart of his book — #HowToBeAnAntiracist — and podcast. Over and over again throughout this conversation, Dr. Kendi took my breath away. His breadth of knowledge, the depth of his expertise, and the honest love that he carries for humanity? This is one for the books.

He spoke of learning from his ancestors and their sacred fights, saying “Individuals fought for what was best for the community, recognizing it was best for themselves.” It struck me that when both of these are simultaneously true, we can be sure that we are doing the right thing. He reminds us all that we can accomplish the seemingly impossible when we actively look out for the community’s well being.

I am deeply honored to have had this conversation. I hope you all enjoy it.

#IbramXKendi #WorkInProgress #WIPSmarties #WIP

My birthday was a flash of sunshine 🧡 From a 4am wake up call for the @todayshow, to surprise videos that made me weep on air from my queens, to oodles of messages from all of you! The texts and calls and hugs from my dearest friends, the doorbell ringing with donuts and flowers, and these sun bursts from my favorite favorite!? I’m a luck lady.

This year was a complex one for so many people. And I feel deeply, truly, incredibly grateful that in the odd spaces it created for so many of us, I’ve gotten to come home. To myself. To my love. To my work (both new and classic), to my truest and deepest friendships, and to reclamation. Of space. Joy. Time. Sisterhood. Empathy. Creativity. A full life. I’m just pinching myself. Everything feels golden. Thank you to all of the people who make this life feel so sparkly and downright GOOD. I love you madly. This cancer season feels like magic. This is already the best year yet. 💛❤️‍🔥🧡

node.text:
Spent my Fourth of July celebrating independence, LA style. Our local Farmer’s Markets support independent growers and farmers, who in turn support all of us with healthy food. Add in the flower tables, music that’s always playing, and local independent business owners selling all kinds of foods from all kind of cultures!? From tamales to kimchi, fresh heirloom tomatoes to oyster mushrooms?! This is MY idea of a party.

And btw, folks discussing the fact that some people (like us ladies) were left out of the 1776 declaration? Pointing out that women and people of color weren’t included in that version of “all men are created equal?” Guys. Those are just plain obvious facts. Speaking truth to power, and drawing a through line from all of us who were left out of that original document to the reality of today where Jim Crow 2.0 is going after the right to vote of communities of color? That’s not an “anti-American rant.” Please. Stop with the hysteria surrounding our actual history. It’s simply a call to not forget the whole truth as we celebrate the parts we view as positive. The whole point is that “all” is supposed to mean “ALL.” As we evolve into better generations — as we have access to science and medicine and social data and more knowledge!? — we are carrying the torch of what should always have been forward with us, so that it may be! So stop with the petty vitriol and the attacks on WOC. A legacy requires truth. To love this country requires seeing this country. After all, when people you love mess up, you help them learn to do better and hold themselves accountable. That’s the kind of growth work celebrating anyhow. I love us. And I want us to be honest so we can be better. Stop attacking Cori and Maxine for holding us to that same standard. It’s gross. It’s also dangerous. Clickbait like that leads to real threats for them. It’s not okay. If their honesty upsets you, you’ve got work to do. I’m sure we all have some, anyhow. So? Let’s be better. That’s how we can build celebrations that are wholly celebratory. Honest love is the only kind of love. That’s how grow. How we bloom, even.

Love to you all. The real kind. ♥️

node.text:
Truth matters, @stevescalise. Especially when the entire globe — and every human living on it — is jointly fighting a once in a (or perhaps more accurately once in three) generation pandemic.

The sharing of genomic sequencing has saved lives. The three decades of research on coronaviruses that predated this zoonotic outbreak of COVID-19 enabled the global medical community to work at a speed never before possible. The innovation, which I testified about yesterday, of American scientists led us to have a vaccine that’s safe and effective in record time. 3.2 billion doses have been administered globally to incredible success. Overall COVID cases are dropping, but only among the vaccinated. The rates of infection, hospitalization, and death among the unvaccinated remain unchanged since January of this year. Facts are, unvaccinated people are contracting and dying from COVID-19. And not just adults. Now COVID-19 is now listed among the top 10 pediatric killers.

Stop enflaming your base. Yes, the global scientific community has work to do on a novel virus. Let them do it. Stop lying to the American people — and the world — from the sacred seat that you are blessed to occupy in Congress. Help America get back on track. Support the administration — after all the data shows that The American Rescue Plan is working — that is doing the work the last one refused to (“I wanted to always play it down. I still like playing it down,” the Former Guy said) and put country over party. As I said in my testimony yesterday, “Science is not partisan. Public health must be supported — to the best of this nation’s ability — by non-partisan political will.”

I also said, “We cannot allow people, no matter if they are anonymous internet marauders, or members of this very governing body, to peddle disinformation that keeps us from protecting ourselves and others.” Ahem.

Contributing to lethal misinformation campaigns is beneath you. And while we’re here, so is trying to score points for shit-posting online when you’re meant to be serving the constituents who elected you. Do better.
